<br>
I did execution 42 times before I finally flagged.  After the 41st pickup group I gave up and had a group of hand-picked friends a uber 65 cleric, 65 warrior, 64 rogue, 63 enchanter, 62 druid and myself as a 60 warrior complete the execution trials.<br>
<br>
Here is some key advice to complete the trials.<br>
<br>
The key to any of the trials is to group with people you know and people who know you and how each of you react to situations that come up in battle.  If you each of you know how to react that is 2/3 of the battle right there.<br>
<br>
Sorry..the bad news is (and I can say this without stretching the truth) these trials were never made for even a group of 61's to get through them.  At the very least 62+ for everyone in group.<br>
<br>
Another hint...when inside waste 4-5 seconds picking which rock mob you will attack or hunting in room for a target.  If you do you will lose.  The MT should go after the first target he sees and while fighting that one be lining up his next target (which direction he will go in for next mob).  This will waste less time.<br>
<br>
Please remember TIME is your enemy in these trials.<br>
NOT ENOUGH DPS would be another concern.<br>
<br>
As the MT always keep the mobs back facing the rogues so they can do maximum damage to any mob you are fighting.  This will result in quicker kills.  Use fast 1h weapons (not the high dam 2h weapons).  You cannot afford to lose aggro even once during the trials.  Yes...I know we warriors can do 40% more damage with those 2h weapons but that is over a period of time.  TIME on each of these battles is very short.<br>
<br>
DO NOT PLAY PING PONG you casters in any trials group.  Play ping pong more than once you will lose precious time and your group will LOSE.  If you want to cast everyone stay close together and not far apart.  A warrior can use shield if a caster gains aggro too much.<br>
<br>
Next suggestion will prolly be flamed..if so flame on.  Do not attempt to banish the rock mobs.  If your caster fails on that attempt HE/SHE will die.  Or they may attempt to banish the named rock mob and will most likely fail and die.  Anyone who dies early in fights results in lesser DPS for group during rest of process.<br>
<br>
Clerics during all waves before executioner...DO NOT use CH.  Use lesser heals but more of them.  Any CH before executioner could/will prolly end up in the instant aggro/death of the cleric.<br>
<br>
When executioner comes then yes..use CH's all you want.<br>
<br>
So to put the trials simply:<br>
<br>
Concentrate on Level<br>
Concentrate on Classes Needed within those levels<br>
Concentrate on how much dps each individual can put out during battle.<br>
Make blasted sure your MT (can be a warrior, sk, or rogue btw) can hold aggro.<br>
Get shaman buffs before you go into trials even if you don't have a shaman in group (also after you get those buffs have shaman zone and come back in to clear aggro)<br>
Make sure EVERYONE is max hasted just before you go in.<br>
So people don't get slowed make sure MR is atleast 200 for all in group, and even those people who argue with me on this one have your DR at least 150 just before you go in.<br>
Don't do an AOE group. (Too much can go wrong with that type group)<br>
And no you can no longer sneak in 30 sec's before exec corpse goes poof and loot the extra marks off of him anymore.<br>
Yes...the execution trial is the easiest.<br>
<br>
But take some wise advice from someone who has done this 42 times.  Do not go in there with 6 level 61's even and think you can win.  Go in there with at least 1 65, 1 64, 1 63, 2 62,s, and one person who needs the flag that is 60 or 61 and if all know the drill you can WIN.<br>
<br>
A warning however.  Getting flagged for Pov and staying alive in PoV are 2 different things.  Once flagged you better know how to play your class very well or you will die quickly in PoV and at 61 you will find a decrease in how fast you get reg EXP and/or AA points compared to when you were 60.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
